[In the past 24 hours, 15 countries, including the USA (160 748), UK (37 717), Brazil (30 891), Iran (26 821), India (24 148), Turkey (23 846), Philippines (22 734), Malaysia (19 307), Russia (18 380), Thailand (16 031), Mexico (15 876), Germany (14 228), Japan (12 730), Viet Nam (12 420), and France (10 969), have reported the highest numbers of cases, all reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. A global total of 10 880 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 7 Sep 2021 to late 8 Sep 2021). There appears to be a weekend-related drop in the reported case numbers. A total of 59 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 33 of the 59 countries are from the European region, 7 are from the Americas region, 6 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the South East Asia region, 6 are from the Western Pacific region, and 2 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 4.9%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 1.9%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 7.5% decrease in daily reported cases and a 10.3% increase in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily report counted over 600 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 224.04 million cumulative reported cases and over 4.62 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
